        <h2>Activity 1- IOT Apps</h2>
        <p>
          An iot application is a prebuilt software service that is used to connect different iot devices together on internet.It provide users an interface to control, record and store data of the devices.
          Collective network of devices connected to Internet.It is a technology that facilitates communication between devices.
        </p>
        <h4>Main Features needed: </h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Sensing</li>
          <li>Connectivity</li>
          <li>Data Processing, storage and security</li>
          <li>User Interface</li>
        </ul>
        <h4>Examples of IOT Applications:</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Google smart home</li>
          <li>Arduino IOT remote</li>
          <li>IP security cameras</li>
          <li>Fitness tracking Applications</li>
          <li>Xiaomi remote controller</li>
        </ul>
        <h2>Activity 2- Smart Building</h2>
        <p>
          Smart stands for ‘Self Monitoring Analysis and Reporting Technology”.Smart devices are the devices which are equipped with positioning and communication technologies.These are integrated into a communication network.
        </p>
        <h4>Main Features needed: </h4>
        <ol>
          <li>Machine Learning</li>
          <li>Artificial Intelligence</li>
          <li>Data sensing through sensors</li>
          <li>CLoud computing and storage</li>
          <li>Connectivity of devices with internet</li>
        </ol>
        <h4>Smart buulding scenarios: </h4>
        <ol>
          <li>Automatic Doors with motion sensors</li>
          <li>Face recognition attendance system</li>
          <li>Motion sensing escalators</li>
          <li>Automatic Temperature controlling(HVAC)</li>
        </ol>
        <h2>Activity 3- Control Interface</h2>
        <p>
          It has been focused on Smart Patient Monitoring System in Hospitals.There are several high-level features of the same like Bi-directional: Processes information, both to and from user, Security policies and Web APIs. Doctors, hospital staff, attendees and patients are the users of this smart system.
          The parts needed are: Room temperature sensor,Oximeter, Blood Pressure sensor, Face & fingerprint recognition automatic door for attendees and many more.
        </p>
